## Actions
Derived this slice from the old stack's final tree by restore-then-trim:
checked out the old files and removed everything that belongs to later
slices. googleAdk.ts here has NO agent-call synthesis (model/tool calls
parent to the invocation root; agent callbacks are no-op stubs) and NO
module-hook auto-instrumentation (explicit plugins:[new WeaveAdkPlugin()]
only). googleAdk.types.ts has no tree-walk fields (parentAgent/subAgents/
findAgent) and no AdkPluginManager/AdkRunnerLike. Tests are the core subset
(single-agent E2E with FLAT parenting assertions, model errors, streaming,
tool error + late afterToolCallback, dangling cleanup, no-client). AGENTS.md
gets the section with transport/duck-typing/lodash bullets only.

## Errors & Mistakes
- The committed googleAdk.ts contained a LITERAL NUL byte as the separator
  in syntheticQueueKey's template string, making grep/file treat the source
  as binary (it rendered invisibly as a space when reading). Replaced with
  the equivalent \0 escape — same runtime string, pure-text source. This is
  the ONE intended content difference vs the old stack's final tree.
- Sandbox 'grep' in Bash is not real grep (empty results are lies); use
  /usr/bin/grep. /usr/bin/grep refused the file as binary until the NUL fix.

